<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-04-0504 </DOCNO><TEXT>Structural components for providing fire-protective separation of buildingsections of nuclear power plants are studied with regard to their relabilitywhen exposed to given effects of fire. The fire effects are determinedby heat balance models and are compared with the effects of standard,reference fire. Reliability is determined statistically by evaluationof standard fire data, and analytically by means of the reliability theory.</TEXT></DOC>